[{"question":"What are you looking at?","answer":"Not yet.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":25,"aSentId":26},{"question":"Dr. Oz, how are you?","answer":"Very, very well.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":40,"aSentId":41},{"question":"What is the best advice for people to get to January and think New Year, new me, new start?","answer":"Well, resolutions actually do make a difference.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":48,"aSentId":49},{"question":"What are the things about the American diet, the way of life, whatever it may be, that are particular, perhaps, to America?","answer":"Well, we have made it easy to do the wrong thing in America.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":64,"aSentId":65},{"question":"Just from French fries?","answer":"Just from French fries.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":74,"aSentId":75},{"question":"If everybody just exercised better portion control, literally cut the amount they ate by, say, a third, what effect would that have on the average life?","answer":"It would dramatically change our life expectancy, but, more importantly, the quality of our life.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":96,"aSentId":97},{"question":"Is it good for America that you have a first lady and president who are obviously very physically fit themselves?","answer":"It\u0027s a huge benefit for the country.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":113,"aSentId":114},{"question":"If you walked as an adult for half an hour a day -- you know, I walk here across Central Park, say, to CNN, and I feel like it\u0027s a pretty good exercise if you walk at a reasonable pace, is that enough to be fit?","answer":"It\u0027s a perfect amount.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":141,"aSentId":142},{"question":"Well, I\u0027m basically in perfect physical (INAUDIBLE)?","answer":"Well, we\u0027re going to --","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":145,"aSentId":146},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":181,"aSentId":182},{"question":"Why do you think you\u0027ve had a -- a battle with your weight?","answer":"If I could figure it out, I\u0027d fix it.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":187,"aSentId":188},{"question":"You don\u0027t know what it is?","answer":"I don\u0027t.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":189,"aSentId":190},{"question":"Did you ever get help for it?","answer":"Sure, plenty of times.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":191,"aSentId":192},{"question":"Where do you -- where do you fall down in terms of dealing with it?","answer":"I eat too much.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":193,"aSentId":194},{"question":"Should they have the jab?","answer":"I think they should have the -- the flu shot, without question.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":234,"aSentId":235},{"question":"What is the best advice, if there is any, for people who get caught up in these terrible tragedies, about how to somehow get back?","answer":"What we ought to, I think, crave, is hope.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":269,"aSentId":270},{"question":"How do you deal with that particular kind of stress, a really -- like a death in the family, a death of a close friend, even, for some people, a death of a beloved pet?","answer":"Because I can\u0027t tell you how many times we\u0027ve lost one couple, a long married couple, and then soon after, we\u0027ll lose the spouse.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":292,"aSentId":293},{"question":"Does that -- does it exist in medical terms, a broken heart?","answer":"There is no question at all that broken hearts exist and they kill people.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":298,"aSentId":299},{"question":"Rhodiola?","answer":"Rhodiola.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":321,"aSentId":322},{"question":"Are you basically telling me you\u0027ve been half cut on vodka your entire career?","answer":"No.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":348,"aSentId":349},{"question":"Can we add a few, you know, cannabis joints to the equation now that they\u0027re legal in some states?","answer":"Cannabis, a fascinating story, in part because there is no question there\u0027s medicinal benefit.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":357,"aSentId":358},{"question":"ORGAN: How addictive is cannabis?","answer":"It\u0027s addictive as cigarettes, in my opinion.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":368,"aSentId":369},{"question":"Is it more dangerous than cigarettes?","answer":"It does -- it has more dangers in part because when you\u0027re under the influence of cannabis, your judgment is a bit more affected than it would be under cigarettes.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":370,"aSentId":371},{"question":"But if you, as one of America\u0027s topmost renowned doctors, says it\u0027s not more dangerous than cigarettes, surely, it should just be legalized, then, right, like cigarettes?","answer":"There are a couple of problems with cannabis.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"But how -- how bad is that, the mass index?","answer":"Well, the body mass index is -- it\u0027s in the overweight category, but I\u0027m not that worried about that.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":446,"aSentId":447},{"question":"What should my waist be?","answer":"Half of your height, half of 73 inches, which is 36 and a half inches.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":452,"aSentId":453},{"question":"How bad is that?","answer":"Well, ideally it would be less than 140.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":477,"aSentId":478},{"question":"What\u0027s mine?","answer":"Thirty-seven.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":485,"aSentId":486},{"question":"I need more healthy cholesterol -- how do I get more healthy cholesterol?","answer":"The best way to do it is to get that waist size down to 36 and a half inches.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":490,"aSentId":491},{"question":"What\u0027s the best way to do that?","answer":"Uh, there are a couple of little tips.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":492,"aSentId":493},{"question":"But can I share that for a second?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":494,"aSentId":495},{"question":"How high?","answer":"It\u0027s supposed to be, ideally, about 115 over 75, ideally.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":509,"aSentId":510},{"question":"And what causes that kind of thing?","answer":"Z: Exercise.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":523,"aSentId":524},{"question":"So what should I be doing to deal with this?","answer":"Well, the -- the number one thing that folks ought to start doing is to automate their lives so the easy decisions are the right ones and are -- and are easier to make.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":557,"aSentId":558},{"question":"Is that bad for me?","answer":"Coffee itself is fine, because it\u0027s a -- it\u0027s the number one source of antioxidants in America.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":579,"aSentId":580},{"question":"-- I\u0027m going to get you back in -- how -- how long would I need to try and really deal with this?","answer":"You could dramatically change these numbers in six weeks.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":599,"aSentId":600},{"question":"Or is it just luck?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s -- it\u0027s a combination.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":640,"aSentId":641},{"question":"So my question to you is, is there a preventative measure that I could use to help alleviate the pain so that, long-term, it won\u0027t turn into arthritis?","answer":"That\u0027s a great question.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":682,"aSentId":683},{"question":"What is the best way to try and deal with it?","answer":"You know, we tackle this on the show a lot because there\u0027s actually 116 million Americans with chronic pain issues.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":685,"aSentId":686},{"question":"And what\u0027s the balance between genetics and just good living?","answer":"It turns out that about two thirds of how long you live is based on your lifestyle.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":717,"aSentId":718},{"question":"What is the secret to long life, do you think, in terms of health?","answer":"Good diet.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":761,"aSentId":762},{"question":"Do what in bed?","answer":"Exactly.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":767,"aSentId":768},{"question":"Mimi -- Mimi, let me ask you, have you ever some kind?","answer":"Never.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":772,"aSentId":773},{"question":"Do you drink alcohol?","answer":"Milk.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":780,"aSentId":781},{"question":"What about that for a recipe for long life?","answer":"It\u0027s obviously worked.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":787,"aSentId":788},{"question":"And if you can\u0027t get enough, what do you do about it?","answer":"The -- the number one under appreciated health problem in America is sleep issues.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":811,"aSentId":812},{"question":"It can\u0027t help you sleep, does it?","answer":"It -- it completely disrupts sleep patterns, and for one very important reason.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":840,"aSentId":841},{"question":"Is that true?","answer":"You cannot get the flu from the flu shot because the material is -- is actually dead flu virus.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":862,"aSentId":863},{"question":"You\u0027re enjoying this, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"This is literally the biggest needle I could find.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":873,"aSentId":874},{"question":"Should children have them?","answer":"It\u0027s recommended that after the age of six months, that we give it to our kids.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":897,"aSentId":898},{"question":"How much of it is mental in the end?","answer":"You know, mental is where you win it all.","docId":"130111pmt","qSentId":922,"aSentId":923}]